Abridged version as I'm sure each party has their own account.  Impudent had refused to resurrect or group with any guild member of Valorous Champions because someone had trained a camp to steal it from a LM member in Sebilis.  Raddoorri claims that his guild never intentionally trains anyone and when he confronted Impudent about it, the situation deteriorated into a name calling/insult slinging match that escalated to the respective guilds' public boards.<br>
<br>
As a leader, you do not have the option of simply saying and doing whatever you want to whomever you want and expect it NOT to reflect on your organization.  Part and parcel of being a leader is the fact that others, both within your organization and outside of it, are going to watch what you say and do and make judgements about you and those you represent.  As a leader, you are held to a higher standard of behavior by others and should conduct yourself accordingly if you want respect from those you lead for your authority and others outside for those you represent.<br>
<br>
As far as presuming or stating everyone in that guild goes around engaging in similiar behavior, I don't agree with that but keep in mind the fact that people do NOT associate extensively with people when their basic values and morals are in conflict.  If a leader engages in (Or think its acceptable behavior.) activities like kill stealing, training, leapfrogging etc. why should John Q. Public think an average member is going to be better than that.  Better yet, why would someone who disagrees with that behavior, remain in a guild who's leadership encourages it?<br>
